             , Surgeon. The Overseers of the Poor desired me to view the Body of the Deceased. Her Arm was bruised, there were 3 or 4 Marks on it, like the Marks made by a Stick, and there was a Wound in the Palm of her Right Hand, above an Inch long, and a quarter of an Inch deep; it seem'd to be a Stab with a Knife. I did not take notice of the small Bruises. On Saturday, the Coroner order'd me to open the Body. - The Abdomen was full of contused Blood, the Womb was rent 7 Inches, and the Infant, which was dead, but full grown, was forced out of the Womb, all but its Feet. The first thing we saw when the Tegament of the Belly was opened, was the Child's Right Hand; and I believe the Fall was the Cause of her and the Child's immediate Death.</p>
