            . About 4 a Clock on Thursday Morning, I was going to wash at a House at Dick's Shore (I am a Washer-woman) and I called at the Prisoner's House for a Pint of Beer; he had got a Pot of Water in his Hand, and he said, Have you heard this unhappy Fate? My Wife has thrown her self out of the Window. I wish you'd carry up this Water, while I draw your Drink. I went up with the Water, and said, How do you do, Mrs. Hallam? How happened this ? Why, says she, I can't tell very well; I unfortunately drop'd my self out of the Window, I feel a Pain in the Bottom of my Belly; but if I should do otherwise than well, there's Anderson and Fleming are so hard-mouth'd, that if my Husband should come to a Tryal, they will swear his Life away; and therefore I beg you would speak in his Behalf, for he is innocent of throwing me out of the Window. The Window has 3 Lights, the Casement is in the middle, it is about a Yard high from the Floor.</p>
