                     <interp inst="t17320114-9-person132" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             , and several other Evidences, appeared in the Prisoner's Behalf, who all gave him the Character of an honest Man.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I can call 20 or 30 more to my Character, but I will give the Court no farther Trouble: I had ten Hours Time to make my Escape, which I should have done, If I had been guilty; but I rather chose to stay and take Care of my Children; and I am as innocent of her going out of the Window, as the Child in the Womb.</p>
               <p>The Jury found the Prisoner <rs id="t17320114-9-verdict54" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17320114-9-verdict54" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs> of both Indictments, and the Court past Sentence of <rs id="t17320114-9-punish55" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17320114-9-punish55" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17320114-9-defend83 t17320114-9-punish55"></join>
               Death
            </rs> upon him accordingly.</p>
            </div1>
